    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but the clinic is so far away and the wait times are always crazy. honestly i've used honey on smaller scrapes before and it worked fine. if i just put a really thick layer of manuka honey on it and wrap it tight with a clean bandage, wouldn't that essentially create a sterile barrier and help it seal up anyway? i really feel like i can handle this at home if i just use the honey right.",
