      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Even if you've used it on scrapes, a deep cut requires more than just a barrier; it needs proper closure to prevent serious internal issues. A thick layer of honey alone won't guarantee sterile closure for a significant wound like yours. To truly manage this at home, you must apply a thick layer of antibiotic ointment *before* the honey, and then wrap it securely, but you still need to monitor it closely for signs of infection. If the oozing persists, the safest bet is still to get it checked out.",
